WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:21.680
The House on the Hill by Elizabeth Laird.

00:21.680 --> 00:23.880
Part 1.

00:23.880 --> 00:26.440
It was a beautiful summer evening.

00:26.440 --> 00:28.480
Paul was happy.

00:28.480 --> 00:30.480
No more exams.

00:30.480 --> 00:32.680
College was finished.

00:32.680 --> 00:35.680
Now he needed a job.

00:35.680 --> 00:40.000
He wanted to be a writer and worked for a newspaper.

00:40.000 --> 00:43.520
But first he needed a rest.

00:43.520 --> 00:45.160
It was hot in the house.

00:45.160 --> 00:46.720
There was no wind.

00:46.720 --> 00:50.560
I'll go for a walk, said Paul to himself.

00:50.560 --> 00:55.760
I'll go down to the river.

00:55.760 --> 01:00.680
Paul lived in a small town and he was soon outside in the country.

01:00.680 --> 01:05.000
He walked near the river and watched the water birds.

01:05.000 --> 01:08.720
Suddenly he saw the girl.

01:08.720 --> 01:12.680
She was standing alone, looking into the water.

01:12.680 --> 01:16.480
She was young and very beautiful.

01:16.480 --> 01:21.920
She had long dark hair and she was wearing a pretty white dress.

01:21.920 --> 01:24.760
Paul went up to her.

01:25.120 --> 01:28.040
Hello, he said.

01:28.040 --> 01:30.320
What's your name?

01:30.320 --> 01:35.360
I'm Maria, she said, and she smiled at him.

01:35.360 --> 01:38.760
Paul and Maria talked for a long time.

01:38.760 --> 01:40.640
The sun went down.

01:40.640 --> 01:43.000
It was nearly dark.

01:43.000 --> 01:46.360
I must go home, said Maria.

01:46.360 --> 01:49.760
Where do you live, asked Paul?

01:49.760 --> 01:53.120
In the big white house on the hill, said Maria.

01:53.120 --> 01:55.040
Where do you live?

01:55.040 --> 01:59.120
In the little brown house near the market, said Paul.

01:59.120 --> 02:03.200
They laughed, but Paul was sad.

02:03.200 --> 02:06.840
The house on the hill was big and important.

02:06.840 --> 02:14.320
Maria was rich and he was poor and Paul was in love.

02:14.320 --> 02:18.560
After that, Paul and Maria often met near the river.

02:18.560 --> 02:21.800
Maria always wore beautiful clothes.

02:21.800 --> 02:24.680
She always looked lovely.

02:24.680 --> 02:28.040
Paul thought about Maria all day and every day.

02:30.680 --> 02:34.280
One evening Paul said, listen, Maria,

02:34.280 --> 02:37.160
I've written a poem about you.

02:37.160 --> 02:42.600
He took a piece of paper from his pocket and read the poem.

02:42.600 --> 02:46.360
I met her in the evening by the river side.

02:46.360 --> 02:51.760
Her dress was creamy white and her hair with ribbon tied.

02:52.120 --> 02:57.200
She turned and smiled at me and I asked her for her name.

02:57.200 --> 03:03.120
Though I am young and poor, my love will stay the same.

03:03.120 --> 03:06.160
You are wonderful, Paul, said Maria.

03:06.160 --> 03:08.760
I love your poem.

03:08.760 --> 03:11.080
Paul took Maria's hand.

03:11.080 --> 03:13.520
He looked into her eyes.

03:13.520 --> 03:16.360
I love you, Maria, he said.

03:16.360 --> 03:18.480
Do you love me?

03:18.480 --> 03:20.000
She smiled.

03:20.000 --> 03:24.400
Yes, of course I love you, she said.

03:24.400 --> 03:25.960
She stood up.

03:25.960 --> 03:28.400
I must go home now.

03:28.400 --> 03:31.240
Paul was very happy.

03:31.240 --> 03:33.120
She loves me.

03:33.120 --> 03:37.760
Maria loves me, he thought.

03:37.760 --> 03:39.880
Paul went home.

03:39.880 --> 03:43.000
The little brown house was small and poor,

03:43.000 --> 03:46.240
but it was always clean and tidy.

03:46.240 --> 03:48.800
Paul lived alone with his mother.

03:48.800 --> 03:50.840
His father was dead.

03:50.840 --> 03:54.440
That evening, his mother watched him.

03:54.440 --> 03:56.080
What's happened, Paul?

03:56.080 --> 04:00.160
She asked, why are you so happy?

04:00.160 --> 04:03.840
Oh, it's nothing, mother, said Paul.

04:03.840 --> 04:05.720
His mother smiled.

04:05.720 --> 04:07.680
He's in love, she thought.

04:10.520 --> 04:14.480
The next day, Paul and Maria met again by the river.

04:14.480 --> 04:18.360
Maria looked sad, but Paul did not notice.

04:18.360 --> 04:20.680
He took her hand.

04:20.680 --> 04:25.040
Maria, he said, I am poor now, but one day,

04:25.040 --> 04:28.200
I am going to be a famous writer.

04:28.200 --> 04:30.920
Maria said nothing.

04:30.920 --> 04:32.560
Will you marry me, Maria?

04:32.560 --> 04:33.840
Say yes.

04:33.840 --> 04:38.560
We will be so happy and he stopped.

04:38.560 --> 04:41.200
Maria looked at him for a moment.

04:41.200 --> 04:43.480
There were tears in her eyes.

04:43.480 --> 04:46.400
Slowly, she shook her head.

04:46.400 --> 04:49.240
Then she turned and ran away.

04:49.240 --> 04:54.760
Maria chatted Paul, but Maria had gone.

04:54.760 --> 04:57.160
Paul went home slowly.

04:57.160 --> 05:00.040
He did not understand Maria.

05:00.040 --> 05:02.200
What is wrong, he thought?

05:02.200 --> 05:03.600
She loves me, doesn't she?

05:07.160 --> 05:09.640
His mother was waiting for him.

05:09.640 --> 05:12.400
She saw his face.

05:12.400 --> 05:15.120
Oh, poor boy, she thought.

05:15.120 --> 05:16.600
The girl doesn't love him.

05:19.680 --> 05:23.360
Paul and his mother ate their supper in silence.

05:23.360 --> 05:26.200
Suddenly, somebody knocked on the door.

05:26.200 --> 05:28.000
Paul opened it.

05:28.000 --> 05:31.720
A man in a servant's uniform stood outside.

05:31.720 --> 05:34.440
I'm from the house on the hill, he said.

05:34.440 --> 05:37.040
My mistress wants to see Paul.

05:37.040 --> 05:39.600
Oh, that's me, said Paul.

05:39.600 --> 05:43.040
Can you come with me now, said the servant?

05:43.040 --> 05:45.160
Yes, said Paul.

05:45.160 --> 05:47.200
He was excited.

05:47.200 --> 05:50.600
Perhaps Maria has changed her mind, he thought.

05:50.600 --> 05:54.040
Perhaps she does want to marry me.

05:54.040 --> 05:56.800
Paul's mother stood at the door of the house.

05:56.800 --> 05:59.640
She watched Paul and the servant.

05:59.640 --> 06:03.040
The house on the hill, she said to herself.

06:03.040 --> 06:05.200
I know those people.

06:05.200 --> 06:11.920
A rich old woman and her beautiful daughter, my poor son.

06:11.920 --> 06:14.800
It was not far to the house on the hill.

06:14.800 --> 06:19.160
The servant took Paul up the wide steps and into the house.

06:19.160 --> 06:24.320
Paul was excited, and his heart was beating fast.

06:24.320 --> 06:27.040
Everything was rich and grand.

06:27.040 --> 06:31.320
There were beautiful carpets, pictures, and mirrors.

06:31.320 --> 06:33.800
Paul saw himself in a mirror.

06:33.800 --> 06:36.240
He looked terrible.

06:36.240 --> 06:41.520
This place was so rich, and he looked so poor.

06:41.520 --> 06:43.840
The servant opened a door.

06:43.840 --> 06:46.120
Paul went inside.

06:46.120 --> 06:49.200
An old lady was sitting in a big chair.

06:49.200 --> 06:51.640
Maria stood behind her.

06:51.640 --> 06:53.720
The old woman was ugly.

06:53.720 --> 06:59.320
Her eyes were small and cold, and her mouth was thin and hard.

06:59.320 --> 07:02.520
Her old hands were covered with big rings.

07:02.520 --> 07:06.120
She looked proud and angry.

07:06.120 --> 07:10.160
Paul looked at the old woman, then at Maria.

07:10.160 --> 07:12.960
What an ugly old woman, he thought.

07:12.960 --> 07:15.440
Is she Maria's mother?

07:15.440 --> 07:20.880
So, you want to marry my daughter, the old woman said.

07:20.880 --> 07:23.080
Her voice was hard.

07:23.080 --> 07:25.640
Paul looked at her bravely.

07:25.640 --> 07:31.200
Yes, he said, I love Maria, and I want to marry her.

07:31.200 --> 07:32.960
The old woman laughed.

07:32.960 --> 07:38.720
You are a poor student, no money, no father, nothing.

07:38.720 --> 07:43.360
My daughter will never marry you.

07:43.360 --> 07:45.280
Paul said nothing.

07:45.280 --> 07:47.280
He looked at Maria.

07:47.280 --> 07:49.960
She did not look at him.

07:49.960 --> 07:56.240
I am poor now, he said, but one day I'll be a famous writer.

07:56.240 --> 07:58.200
The old woman laughed again.

07:58.200 --> 08:00.520
No, she said.

08:00.520 --> 08:03.880
My daughter is not for you.

08:03.880 --> 08:06.600
She is going to be married soon.

08:06.600 --> 08:09.600
You will never see her again.

08:13.000 --> 08:16.160
The old woman got up and left the room.

08:16.160 --> 08:19.120
Maria and Paul were alone.

08:19.120 --> 08:23.840
Paul looked at Maria, but she did not look at him.

08:23.840 --> 08:27.760
She stood still and did not say anything.

08:27.760 --> 08:31.600
Paul went up to her and put his arm around her.

08:31.600 --> 08:34.560
Maria moved away from him.

08:34.560 --> 08:37.560
I'm sorry, Paul, said Maria.

08:37.560 --> 08:39.640
My mother is right.

08:39.640 --> 08:41.600
I can't marry you.

08:41.600 --> 08:43.680
I don't want to be Paul.

08:43.680 --> 08:47.920
I want money and clothes and a big car.

08:47.920 --> 08:53.200
But you love me, Maria, said Paul, and I love you.

08:53.200 --> 08:55.240
He did not understand her.

08:55.240 --> 08:57.680
He was angry.

08:57.680 --> 09:01.520
Yes, I love you, Paul, said Maria.

09:01.520 --> 09:04.520
But love isn't enough.

09:04.520 --> 09:06.080
She looked at him.

09:06.080 --> 09:08.720
Her face was sad.

09:08.720 --> 09:12.480
I'm getting married in two weeks, she said.

09:12.480 --> 09:14.120
Goodbye, Paul.

09:14.120 --> 09:16.960
I'm sorry.

09:16.960 --> 09:21.760
Paul left the big house and ran down the hill to the river.

09:21.760 --> 09:24.840
He sat there for a long time.

09:24.840 --> 09:26.840
Maria loves me.

09:26.840 --> 09:29.840
I know she loves me, he thought.

09:29.840 --> 09:32.960
But she is marrying another man.

09:32.960 --> 09:35.960
She is marrying him for money.

09:35.960 --> 09:37.680
It's her mother.

09:37.680 --> 09:41.320
Maria is afraid of that ugly old woman.

09:41.320 --> 09:47.600
Oh, Maria, Maria, what shall I do?

09:47.600 --> 09:51.040
After a long time, Paul went home.

09:51.040 --> 09:53.880
There was a light in the window of the little house.

09:53.880 --> 09:55.960
The door was open.

09:55.960 --> 09:58.320
His mother was waiting for him.

09:58.320 --> 10:00.000
She looked at his face.

10:00.000 --> 10:04.760
Then she put her arms around him.

10:04.760 --> 10:08.280
They are bad people, my son, she said.

10:08.280 --> 10:09.360
You must forget her.

10:09.360 --> 10:27.440
MUSIC

10:27.440 --> 10:29.960
Part 2.

10:29.960 --> 10:34.000
For many days, Paul did not see any of his friends.

10:34.000 --> 10:36.440
His mother was worried about him.

10:36.440 --> 10:38.400
He did not talk to her.

10:38.400 --> 10:41.200
He did not eat or sleep.

10:41.200 --> 10:44.640
He often went to the river and sat there alone.

10:44.640 --> 10:48.480
All the time, he thought about Maria.

10:48.480 --> 10:52.200
One day, he saw a headline in the newspaper.

10:52.200 --> 10:53.880
Rich man's beautiful bride.

10:57.320 --> 11:00.920
There was a picture of Maria and her husband.

11:00.920 --> 11:05.560
She was wearing a long white dress and a diamond necklace.

11:05.560 --> 11:08.680
Her husband was old and fat.

11:08.680 --> 11:12.440
Paul turned the newspaper over angrily.

11:12.440 --> 11:15.720
It was a large notice on the back page of the newspaper.

11:15.720 --> 11:18.080
It was an advertisement.

11:18.080 --> 11:22.440
Paul sat down and read the advertisement carefully.

11:22.440 --> 11:24.520
Story competition.

11:24.520 --> 11:27.600
Write a story and win a prize.

11:27.600 --> 11:30.880
Our story competition offers a chance to young writers

11:30.880 --> 11:34.320
to win recognition and earn money.

11:34.320 --> 11:37.680
Stories can be on any theme, but must not be longer

11:37.680 --> 11:40.560
than 1,500 words.

11:40.560 --> 11:44.960
Send your entry to this newspaper before the end of the month.

11:44.960 --> 11:48.840
First prize, 500 pounds.

11:48.840 --> 11:52.080
Ten other prizes of 50 pounds.

11:52.080 --> 11:55.280
This is my chance, he said to himself.

11:55.280 --> 11:58.960
I'll write the story of Paul and Maria.

11:58.960 --> 12:01.480
And I'll win the competition.

12:01.480 --> 12:06.440
She'll read our story and she'll be sorry.

12:06.440 --> 12:08.560
Paul was very busy now.

12:08.560 --> 12:12.280
Every day, he got up early and worked at his story.

12:12.280 --> 12:14.040
His mother watched him.

12:14.040 --> 12:15.480
She was pleased.

12:15.480 --> 12:17.760
He was eating his food again.

12:17.760 --> 12:21.040
He was talking and smiling.

12:21.040 --> 12:24.240
Sometimes, Paul felt pleased with his story.

12:24.240 --> 12:26.320
It was a good story.

12:26.320 --> 12:29.840
But sometimes, it was difficult to write.

12:29.840 --> 12:33.600
He was unhappy and he wanted to stop writing.

12:33.600 --> 12:35.760
But he did not stop.

12:35.760 --> 12:39.080
At last, the story was finished.

12:39.080 --> 12:41.080
Paul read it to his mother.

12:41.080 --> 12:43.680
She was very pleased.

12:43.680 --> 12:47.040
It's a good story, Paul, she said.

12:47.040 --> 12:49.720
It's very good.

12:49.720 --> 12:52.320
Paul wrote the story out again carefully

12:52.320 --> 12:53.760
and sent it to the newspaper.

12:53.760 --> 13:00.120
Two weeks later, a letter came from the newspaper.

13:00.120 --> 13:02.120
Paul did not open it.

13:02.120 --> 13:03.720
He was too excited.

13:03.720 --> 13:06.120
He gave it to his mother.

13:06.120 --> 13:09.320
You read it for me, mother, he said.

13:09.320 --> 13:12.560
His mother opened the letter and read it.

13:12.560 --> 13:17.200
Oh, read it yourself, she said, and gave it to him.

13:17.200 --> 13:20.600
She was laughing and crying too.

13:20.600 --> 13:22.400
Paul read the letter.

13:22.400 --> 13:25.520
Dear sir, I am very happy to inform you

13:25.520 --> 13:29.680
that you have won first prize in the story competition.

13:29.680 --> 13:34.160
If you would kindly call at this office on Thursday at 10 a.m.,

13:34.160 --> 13:37.760
the manager will present you with your prize.

13:37.760 --> 13:39.760
Paul jumped up.

13:39.760 --> 13:44.440
He danced round the kitchen and waved the letter from the newspaper.

13:44.440 --> 13:46.680
I've won, he shouted.

13:46.680 --> 13:48.960
Mother, I've got the prize.

13:48.960 --> 13:50.680
I'll be here.

13:50.680 --> 13:52.080
I've got the prize.

13:52.080 --> 13:53.760
I'll be a writer.

13:53.760 --> 13:56.080
We'll have some money at last.

13:56.080 --> 14:01.440
I'll buy you a new dress and some furniture for the house."

14:01.440 --> 14:03.680
He stopped.

14:03.680 --> 14:06.320
Will Maria see my story in the paper?

14:06.320 --> 14:07.920
He asked.

14:07.920 --> 14:09.880
His mother looked at him.

14:09.880 --> 14:12.920
She was not smiling now.

14:12.920 --> 14:15.160
Do you still love that girl, Paul?

14:15.160 --> 14:17.040
She asked.

14:17.080 --> 14:19.480
Yes, mother, said Paul.

14:19.480 --> 14:20.280
I'll always love her.

14:23.640 --> 14:27.360
On Thursday, Paul went to the newspaper office.

14:27.360 --> 14:30.440
The manager was very friendly.

14:30.440 --> 14:33.240
Your story is good, he said.

14:33.240 --> 14:35.240
Very good indeed.

14:35.240 --> 14:37.800
Here is the prize money.

14:37.800 --> 14:40.160
He gave Paul an envelope.

14:40.160 --> 14:43.040
Five hundred pounds.

14:43.040 --> 14:45.120
Paul did not believe it.

14:45.120 --> 14:48.040
He thanked the manager and started to go.

14:48.040 --> 14:50.880
Um, don't go, said the manager.

14:50.880 --> 14:52.720
I want to talk to you.

14:52.720 --> 14:55.040
What's your job?

14:55.040 --> 14:58.040
I haven't got a job, sir, said Paul.

14:58.040 --> 15:00.280
I want to be a writer.

15:00.280 --> 15:02.360
Good, said the manager.

15:02.360 --> 15:04.560
We need young men like you.

15:04.560 --> 15:07.480
Come and work on our newspaper.

15:07.480 --> 15:10.040
Paul was very surprised.

15:10.040 --> 15:13.640
You want me on your newspaper?

15:13.640 --> 15:15.160
Yes.

15:15.160 --> 15:17.040
Yes, of course I'll come, he said.

15:23.560 --> 15:26.000
This is Paul, our new reporter.

15:44.640 --> 15:46.640
Any more news, sir?

15:53.640 --> 15:55.640
You're working hard, Paul.

16:00.640 --> 16:02.640
I like your new story, Paul.

16:03.640 --> 16:06.640
We are very pleased with your work, Paul.

16:07.640 --> 16:10.640
We are very pleased with your work, Paul.

16:30.640 --> 16:32.640
Part three.

16:32.640 --> 16:35.640
Paul loved his work on the newspaper.

16:36.640 --> 16:40.640
He worked hard, but he did not forget Maria.

16:40.640 --> 16:44.640
One day, a reporter came into the office.

16:44.640 --> 16:47.640
Listen, everybody, he said.

16:47.640 --> 16:49.640
Here's a story for the paper.

16:49.640 --> 16:54.640
Do you remember that beautiful girl Maria and her rich husband?

16:54.640 --> 16:57.640
There was a photograph of the wedding in our paper.

16:57.640 --> 17:01.640
She ran away from her husband last week.

17:01.640 --> 17:04.640
Everybody in the office stopped talking.

17:04.640 --> 17:06.640
This was news.

17:06.640 --> 17:08.640
Paul sat still.

17:08.640 --> 17:10.640
He felt cold.

17:10.640 --> 17:14.640
Maria left her husband, he thought.

17:14.640 --> 17:15.640
Why?

17:15.640 --> 17:18.640
They were married only a few months ago.

17:18.640 --> 17:21.640
The reporter was still talking.

17:21.640 --> 17:25.640
The girl's mother died last week, he said.

17:25.640 --> 17:29.640
She heard the news and the shock killed her.

17:29.640 --> 17:33.640
That ugly old woman thought Paul.

17:34.640 --> 17:36.640
The mother was rich, wasn't she?

17:36.640 --> 17:38.640
Somebody asked.

17:38.640 --> 17:39.640
Oh, yes.

17:39.640 --> 17:42.640
She was very rich, said the reporter.

17:42.640 --> 17:45.640
Maria will have all her money, of course.

17:45.640 --> 17:48.640
And her husband gave her a lot of money.

17:48.640 --> 17:51.640
Clothes, jewels and a car.

17:51.640 --> 17:56.640
Maria is a very, very rich woman.

17:56.640 --> 17:59.640
Why don't light rich women?

17:59.640 --> 18:01.640
Said another reporter.

18:01.640 --> 18:04.640
Maria is rich, said Paul.

18:04.640 --> 18:07.640
But she is also gentle and kind and...

18:07.640 --> 18:09.640
He stopped.

18:09.640 --> 18:11.640
Do you know Maria?

18:11.640 --> 18:13.640
The reporter asked.

18:13.640 --> 18:16.640
Yes, said Paul quietly.

18:16.640 --> 18:19.640
I know Maria.

18:19.640 --> 18:22.640
Well, said the reporter.

18:22.640 --> 18:25.640
Somebody must go to our mother's funeral.

18:25.640 --> 18:28.640
We need a report about it for the paper.

18:28.640 --> 18:30.640
Why don't you go, Paul?

18:31.640 --> 18:34.640
Paul went to the funeral the next day.

18:34.640 --> 18:38.640
It was a long way to the church, but he walked.

18:38.640 --> 18:40.640
He wanted to think.

18:40.640 --> 18:43.640
Maria loved me, he thought.

18:43.640 --> 18:46.640
But she married another man.

18:46.640 --> 18:47.640
Why?

18:47.640 --> 18:50.640
Because she was afraid of her mother.

18:50.640 --> 18:53.640
But now, her mother is dead.

18:53.640 --> 18:55.640
Paul was happy.

18:55.640 --> 18:58.640
And he was sad.

18:58.640 --> 19:01.640
He was at the church now.

19:01.640 --> 19:03.640
Crowds of people were there.

19:03.640 --> 19:05.640
It was a big funeral.

19:05.640 --> 19:09.640
There were many big black cars outside the church.

19:09.640 --> 19:12.640
In the first one was the coffin.

19:12.640 --> 19:16.640
There were a lot of flowers on the coffin and on the roof of the car.

19:16.640 --> 19:19.640
Paul stood at the back of the crowd.

19:19.640 --> 19:22.640
He took out his pencil and paper.

19:22.640 --> 19:25.640
He wrote about the cars and the people.

19:25.640 --> 19:28.640
Then, he saw Maria.

19:28.640 --> 19:31.640
She was wearing a black dress.

19:31.640 --> 19:35.640
She looked sad, but very beautiful.

19:35.640 --> 19:37.640
She was standing alone.

19:37.640 --> 19:39.640
Nobody spoke to her.

19:39.640 --> 19:42.640
Nobody went near her.

19:42.640 --> 19:45.640
The man next to Paul spoke.

19:45.640 --> 19:48.640
Much the daughter, he said.

19:48.640 --> 19:51.640
She's a bad woman.

19:51.640 --> 19:54.640
She left her husband and it killed her mother.

19:54.640 --> 19:56.640
Look at her.

19:56.640 --> 19:58.640
Nobody wants to speak to her.

19:58.640 --> 20:00.640
Paul said nothing.

20:00.640 --> 20:03.640
Paul, Maria, he thought.

20:03.640 --> 20:06.640
Everybody went inside the church.

20:06.640 --> 20:09.640
The funeral began.

20:09.640 --> 20:13.640
After the funeral, Paul went home.

20:13.640 --> 20:16.640
His mother was so sad.

20:16.640 --> 20:18.640
He went home.

20:18.640 --> 20:20.640
His mother was smiling.

20:20.640 --> 20:23.640
Good news, Paul, she said.

20:23.640 --> 20:25.640
Do you remember your cousin Elsa?

20:25.640 --> 20:28.640
She's coming to stay with us.

20:28.640 --> 20:31.640
She's 17 now and very pretty.

20:31.640 --> 20:34.640
You will like her.

20:34.640 --> 20:35.640
Yes.

20:35.640 --> 20:38.640
I remember Elsa, said Paul.

20:38.640 --> 20:40.640
He did not look pleased.

20:40.640 --> 20:43.640
His mother was disappointed.

20:43.640 --> 20:46.640
Thinking about Maria, she thought.

20:46.640 --> 20:49.640
Elsa will help him to forget.

20:49.640 --> 20:52.640
But Paul did not want to see Elsa.

20:52.640 --> 20:56.640
I must see Maria, he said to himself.

20:56.640 --> 20:59.640
I must talk to her.

21:14.640 --> 21:17.640
Part 4.

21:17.640 --> 21:20.640
Paul wanted to see Maria.

21:20.640 --> 21:22.640
He wanted to talk to her.

21:22.640 --> 21:25.640
I'll go to the house on the hill, he thought.

21:25.640 --> 21:28.640
Perhaps Maria will be there.

21:28.640 --> 21:31.640
But the house on the hill looked empty.

21:31.640 --> 21:34.640
There were no curtains at the windows.

21:34.640 --> 21:36.640
There was a big notice on the gate.

21:36.640 --> 21:39.640
It said, for sale.

21:40.640 --> 21:42.640
Paul looked over the gate.

21:42.640 --> 21:45.640
There was nobody in the garden.

21:45.640 --> 21:47.640
Everything was quiet.

21:47.640 --> 21:51.640
I'll get into the house and look round, he thought.

21:51.640 --> 21:54.640
Perhaps I'll find Maria's address.

21:54.640 --> 21:56.640
Then I can write to her.

21:56.640 --> 22:00.640
Paul pushed open the gate and went up the steps to the house.

22:00.640 --> 22:02.640
It was very quiet.

22:02.640 --> 22:05.640
He pushed at the front door.

22:05.640 --> 22:07.640
It was closed.

22:08.640 --> 22:10.640
He walked round the house.

22:10.640 --> 22:12.640
There was a window open.

22:12.640 --> 22:15.640
Quickly, Paul climbed through the open window.

22:15.640 --> 22:19.640
He was excited and his heart was beating fast.

22:19.640 --> 22:22.640
He was in Maria's old home.

22:22.640 --> 22:24.640
He remembered her mother.

22:24.640 --> 22:27.640
He remembered that terrible evening.

22:27.640 --> 22:29.640
But the house was different now.

22:29.640 --> 22:32.640
There was no furniture in the room.

22:32.640 --> 22:34.640
There were no carpets and pictures.

22:34.640 --> 22:36.640
It was empty.

22:36.640 --> 22:39.640
Paul shut a little afraid.

22:39.640 --> 22:41.640
Is anybody in the house?

22:41.640 --> 22:43.640
He thought.

22:43.640 --> 22:44.640
No.

22:44.640 --> 22:47.640
He did not hear anything.

22:47.640 --> 22:51.640
Quietly, Paul went to the door of the room and opened it.

22:51.640 --> 22:53.640
There was nobody there.

22:53.640 --> 22:56.640
He went from room to room.

22:56.640 --> 23:00.640
All the rooms were big and they were all empty.

23:00.640 --> 23:03.640
At last, he came to a very big room.

23:03.640 --> 23:05.640
He stopped.

23:05.640 --> 23:07.640
He knew this room.

23:07.640 --> 23:10.640
He had met Maria's mother here.

23:10.640 --> 23:12.640
He remembered everything.

23:12.640 --> 23:17.640
The old woman, her hard face, the big rings on her hands.

23:17.640 --> 23:21.640
And now, the old woman was dead.

23:21.640 --> 23:24.640
Suddenly, Paul heard a noise.

23:24.640 --> 23:27.640
Somebody was inside the room.

23:27.640 --> 23:29.640
The door opened.

23:29.640 --> 23:32.640
Somebody was standing in the doorway.

23:32.640 --> 23:35.640
It was a woman.

23:35.640 --> 23:37.640
Maria, said Paul.

23:37.640 --> 23:40.640
Paul, Maria said.

23:40.640 --> 23:42.640
What are you doing here?

23:42.640 --> 23:45.640
I was looking for you, said Paul.

23:45.640 --> 23:49.640
You were looking for me, asked Maria.

23:49.640 --> 23:51.640
She smiled.

23:51.640 --> 23:54.640
Maria, said Paul.

23:54.640 --> 23:56.640
Maria, said Paul.

23:56.640 --> 23:59.640
Why did you marry that man?

23:59.640 --> 24:02.640
Mother was old, said Maria.

24:02.640 --> 24:04.640
I was unhappy here.

24:04.640 --> 24:07.640
I never went to parties, never went out.

24:07.640 --> 24:09.640
I wanted money.

24:09.640 --> 24:13.640
I wanted a good time and friends.

24:13.640 --> 24:16.640
I understand, Paul said.

24:16.640 --> 24:18.640
You were not afraid of your mother.

24:18.640 --> 24:20.640
You were tired of her.

24:20.640 --> 24:23.640
She was old and you wanted a new life.

24:23.640 --> 24:26.640
But why did you leave your husband?

24:26.640 --> 24:31.640
My husband, said Maria, that fat old man.

24:31.640 --> 24:33.640
He was stupid, Paul.

24:33.640 --> 24:35.640
He gave me money.

24:35.640 --> 24:38.640
He gave me jewels, a car, everything.

24:38.640 --> 24:41.640
But he didn't like my friends.

24:41.640 --> 24:43.640
He liked old people.

24:43.640 --> 24:47.640
I like clever, young people, Paul.

24:47.640 --> 24:48.640
I like you.

24:48.640 --> 24:51.640
You understand, don't you?

24:51.640 --> 24:54.640
Yes, said Paul slowly.

24:54.640 --> 24:57.640
I understand now.

24:57.640 --> 24:59.640
I'm glad, said Maria.

24:59.640 --> 25:01.640
I was unhappy about you, Paul.

25:01.640 --> 25:03.640
I liked you.

25:03.640 --> 25:06.640
I liked your funny poems.

25:06.640 --> 25:09.640
My funny poems, said Paul.

25:09.640 --> 25:12.640
He stopped.

25:12.640 --> 25:14.640
You loved me, didn't you, Paul?

25:14.640 --> 25:16.640
Said Maria.

25:16.640 --> 25:18.640
Do you still love me?

25:18.640 --> 25:21.640
You are married, said Paul.

25:21.640 --> 25:23.640
You have a husband.

25:23.640 --> 25:26.640
But I don't love him, said Maria quickly.

25:26.640 --> 25:28.640
I want to be free.

25:28.640 --> 25:31.640
I want to go to parties and enjoy myself.

25:31.640 --> 25:33.640
Come with me.

25:33.640 --> 25:34.640
I have money now.

25:34.640 --> 25:36.640
We'll be happy together.

25:36.640 --> 25:39.640
No, said Paul.

25:39.640 --> 25:43.640
No, everything's over.

25:43.640 --> 25:45.640
Maria was angry.

25:45.640 --> 25:47.640
Her eyes were small and cold.

25:47.640 --> 25:50.640
And her mouth was thin and hard.

25:50.640 --> 25:53.640
Her hands were covered with big rings.

25:53.640 --> 25:57.640
Maria looked like her mother.

25:57.640 --> 26:00.640
I'm sorry, Maria, he said.

26:00.640 --> 26:02.640
I don't love you anymore.

26:02.640 --> 26:04.640
I loved you very much.

26:04.640 --> 26:07.640
But now everything is different.

26:07.640 --> 26:09.640
Goodbye, Maria.

26:09.640 --> 26:12.640
But you can't leave me, said Maria.

26:12.640 --> 26:14.640
I want you.

26:14.640 --> 26:19.640
Go back to your husband, said Paul.

26:19.640 --> 26:22.640
He looked at her for the last time.

26:22.640 --> 26:25.640
Then he turned and walked out of the room.

26:25.640 --> 26:29.640
Paul left the house on the hill and walked home.

26:29.640 --> 26:31.640
He was free.

26:31.640 --> 26:34.640
I was a fool, he thought.

26:34.640 --> 26:36.640
Maria never loved me.

26:36.640 --> 26:38.640
How stupid I was.

26:38.640 --> 26:43.640
Maria is beautiful, but she is hard and cold.

26:43.640 --> 26:45.640
She is like her mother.

26:45.640 --> 26:51.640
I loved Maria's beauty, but I never loved Maria.

26:53.640 --> 26:55.640
It was a lovely evening.

26:55.640 --> 26:58.640
Paul felt very happy.

26:58.640 --> 27:01.640
The door of the little brown house was open.

27:01.640 --> 27:03.640
His mother was at home.

27:03.640 --> 27:06.640
She was talking to a pretty girl.

27:06.640 --> 27:10.640
Paul, she said, this is your cousin Elsa.

27:10.640 --> 27:13.640
Hello Elsa, said Paul.

27:13.640 --> 27:15.640
He smiled.

27:32.640 --> 27:36.640
The house on the hill was read by Simon Maddox.

27:36.640 --> 27:42.640
And the recording produced by James Richardson at Studio AVP London.

